  "ComponentName": "Mk82 Railgun",
  "LongDescription": "The Mk.82 provides an extra rail, giving the attached warship double the anti-ship firepower. However, because of the higher need for a dedicated power line to combat the incredibly slow recharge time, the Mk.82 requires even larger amounts of reactor power and crew to properly function. Fires 300mm magnetic rounds.",
  "FlavorText": "When the Mk81 took off, the Naval Office immediately started talking about improving on the railgun, especially since the after-action reports described the Mk81 being one of the most deadly weapons to be developed since the Mk62. Only problem was that it's- understandably- quite expensive to produce in-house, so the Naval Office turned to a third-party.\n\nThe initial design was such a complete and utter failure that the entire team was pulled from the project and the company slated for \"liquidation\" before the weapon was given to Falke-Tethys and thus, the Mk82 was put into service after a three-year development time and has since become a symbol of Alliance strength. Doesn't seem to stop the OSP, though.\n\n- T. Meadows, LT",
